ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fprison-guards-in-uk-hospitalised-after-inmates-spike-staff-curry-with-dangerous-drug-5681326%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UN%20Revises%20India's%202024%20Economic%20Growth%20Projection%20Upwards%20From%206.2%20To%206.9%25%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20Nations%20has%20revised%20upwards%20India's%20growth%20projections%20for%202024%2C%20with%20the%20country's%20economy%20now%20forecast%20to%20expand%20by%20close%20to%20seven%20per%20cent%20this%20year%2C%20mainly%20driven%20by%20strong%20public%20investment%20and%20resilient%20private%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Economic%20Situation%20and%20Prospects%20as%20of%20mid-2024%2C%20released%20Thursday%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIndia's%20economy%20is%20forecast%20to%20expand%20by%206.9%20per%20cent%20in%202024%20and%206.6%20per%20cent%20in%202025%2C%20mainly%20driven%20by%20strong%20public%20investment%20and%20resilient%20private%20consumption.%20Although%20subdued%20external%20demand%20will%20continue%20to%20weigh%20on%20merchandise%20export%20growth%2C%20pharmaceuticals%20and%20chemicals%20exports%20are%20expected%20to%20expand%20strongly.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%206.9%20per%20cent%20economic%20growth%20projections%20for%20India%20in%20the%20mid-year%20update%20is%20an%20upward%20revision%20from%20the%206.2%20per%20cent%20GDP%20forecast%20made%20by%20the%20UN%20in%20January%20this%20year.%20The%20UN%20World%20Economic%20Situation%20and%20Prospects%20(WESP)%202024%20report%20that%20was%20launched%20in%20January%20had%20said%20that%20growth%20in%20India%20was%20projected%20to%20reach%206.2%20per%20cent%20in%202024%2C%20amid%20robust%20domestic%20demand%20and%20strong%20growth%20in%20the%20manufacturing%20and%20services%20sectors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20projection%20in%20January%20for%20India's%20GDP%20growth%20for%202025%20remains%20unchanged%20at%206.6%20per%20cent%20in%20the%20latest%20assessment%20of%20the%20economic%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20update%20said%20that%20consumer%20price%20inflation%20in%20India%20is%20projected%20to%20decelerate%20from%205.6%20per%20cent%20in%202023%20to%204.5%20per%20cent%20in%202024%2C%20staying%20within%20the%20central%20bank's%20two%20to%20six%20per%20cent%20medium-term%20target%20range.%20Similarly%2C%20inflation%20rates%20in%20other%20South%20Asian%20countries%20declined%20in%202023%20and%20are%20expected%20to%20decelerate%20further%20in%202024%2C%20ranging%20from%202.2%20per%20cent%20in%20the%20Maldives%20to%2033.6%20per%20cent%20in%20Iran.%20Despite%20some%20moderation%2C%20food%20prices%20remained%20elevated%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20especially%20in%20Bangladesh%20and%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20labour%20market%20indicators%20have%20also%20improved%20amid%20robust%20growth%20and%20higher%20labour%20force%20participation%2C%20it%20said.%20India's%20government%20remains%20committed%20to%20gradually%20reduce%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%2C%20while%20seeking%20to%20increase%20capital%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Asia's%20economic%20outlook%20is%20expected%20to%20remain%20strong%2C%20supported%20by%20a%20robust%20performance%20of%20India's%20economy%20and%20a%20slight%20recovery%20in%20Pakistan%20and%20Sri%20Lanka.%20Regional%20GDP%20is%20projected%20to%20grow%20by%205.8%20per%20cent%20in%202024%20(an%20upward%20revision%20of%200.6%20percentage%20points%20since%20January)%20and%205.7%20per%20cent%20in%202025%2C%20below%20the%206.2%20per%20cent%20recorded%20in%202023.%20However%2C%20still%20tight%20financial%20conditions%20and%20fiscal%20and%20external%20imbalances%20will%20continue%20to%20weigh%20on%20South%20Asia's%20growth%20performance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20potential%20increases%20in%20energy%20prices%20amid%20geopolitical%20tensions%20and%20the%20ongoing%20disruption%20in%20the%20Red%20Sea%20pose%20a%20risk%20to%20the%20regional%20economic%20outlook%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20economy%20is%20now%20forecast%20to%20grow%20by%202.7%20per%20cent%20in%202024%20(an%20increase%20of%200.3%20percentage%20points%20from%20the%20forecast%20in%20January)%20and%202.8%20per%20cent%20in%202025%20(an%20increase%20of%200.1%20percentage%20points).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20upward%20revisions%20mainly%20reflect%20a%20better%20outlook%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20where%20the%20latest%20forecast%20points%20to%202.3%20per%20cent%20growth%20in%202024%20(an%20upward%20revision%20of%200.9%20percentage%20points%20since%20January)%2C%20and%20several%20large%20emerging%20economies%2C%20notably%20Brazil%2C%20India%20and%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20noted%20that%20several%20large%20developing%20economies%20-%20Indonesia%2C%20India%20and%20Mexico%20-%20are%20benefiting%20from%20strong%20domestic%20and%20external%20demand.%20In%20comparison%2C%20many%20economies%20in%20Africa%20and%20Latin%20America%20and%20the%20Caribbean%20are%20on%20a%20low-growth%20trajectory%2C%20facing%20high%20inflation%2C%20elevated%20borrowing%20costs%2C%20persistent%20exchange%20rate%20pressures%20and%20lingering%20political%20instability.%20The%20possible%20intensification%20and%20spreading%20of%20conflicts%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20Red%20Sea%20add%20further%20uncertainties%20to%20the%20near-term%20outlook%20for%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20the%20mid-year%20update%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobal%20trade%20is%20expected%20to%20recover%20in%202024.%20The%20early%20boost%20to%20trade%20flows%20in%20the%20first%20months%20of%20the%20year%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20destocking%20of%20the%20inventory%20that%20piled%20up%20amid%20supply-chain%20disruptions%20in%202021-22.%20%26quot%3BChina's%20foreign%20trade%20grew%20faster%20than%20expected%20in%20the%20first%20two%20months%20in%202024%2C%20driven%20largely%20by%20exports%20to%20emerging%20markets%2C%20particularly%20to%20Brazil%2C%20India%20and%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20persistent%20geopolitical%20tensions%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20disruptions%20in%20the%20Red%20Sea%2C%20and%20escalating%20cost%20of%20freight%20continue%20to%20pose%20challenges%20to%20global%20trade%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mid-year%20update%20said%20global%20economic%20prospects%20have%20improved%20since%20January%2C%20with%20major%20economies%20avoiding%20a%20severe%20downturn%2C%20bringing%20down%20inflation%20without%20increasing%20unemployment.%20However%2C%20the%20outlook%20is%20only%20cautiously%20optimistic.%20Higher-for-longer%20interest%20rates%2C%20debt%20sustainability%20challenges%2C%20continuing%20geopolitical%20tensions%20and%20ever-worsening%20climate%20risks%20continue%20to%20pose%20challenges%20to%20growth%2C%20threatening%20decades%20of%20development%20gains%2C%20especially%20for%20least%20developed%20countries%20and%20small%20island%20developing%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20outlook%20for%20China%20registers%20a%20small%20uptick%20with%20growth%20now%20expected%20to%20be%204.8%20per%20cent%20in%202024%2C%20from%204.7%20per%20cent%20projected%20in%20January.%20China's%20growth%20is%20projected%20to%20moderate%20to%204.8%20per%20cent%20in%202024%2C%20from%205.2%20per%20cent%20in%202023.%20Pent-up%20consumer%20demand%20-%20released%20after%20the%20lifting%20of%20pandemic-related%20restrictions%20-%20has%20largely%20dissipated.%20While%20enhanced%20policy%20support%20is%20expected%20to%20boost%20investments%20in%20public%20infrastructure%20and%20strategic%20sectors%2C%20the%20property%20sector%20poses%20a%20significant%20downside%20risk%20to%20the%20Chinese%20economy%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715912160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2F0rqgd4ho_india-economy-generic-reuters_62