avoured%20entering%20into%20a%20conversation%20with%20the%20Indian%20leadership%20on%20their%20concerns%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIndia%20was%20colonized%20for%20over%20100%20years.%20So%2C%20when%20we're%20having%20a%20conversation%20about%20human%20rights%2C%20and%20you're%20having%20a%20conversation%20with%20(External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S)%20Jai%20Shankar%20or%20someone%20else%2C%20you%20have%20to%20understand%20that%20just%20coming%20in%20from%20a%20perspective%20of%20lecturing%20India.%20When%20they%20say%20that%20we've%20had%20colonial%20powers%20lecture%20us%20for%20hundreds%20of%20years%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20productive%2C%26quot%3B%20Congressman%20Ro%20Khanna%20told%20members%20of%20the%20Indian%20American%20community%20during%20the%20%26quot%3BDesi%20Decides%26quot%3B%20Summit%20of%20Indian%20American%20Impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhanna%2C%20who%20is%20also%20co-chair%20of%20the%20Congressional%20India%20Caucus%2C%20was%20joined%20by%20three%20other%20Indian%20American%20lawmakers%20--%20Shri%20Thanedar%2C%20Pramila%20Jayapal%20and%20Dr%20Ami%20Bera%20--%20during%20the%20panel%20discussion%2C%20which%20was%20moderated%20by%20Zohreen%20Shah%2C%20ABC%20national%20correspondent%2C%20who%20asked%20them%20about%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20relations%20with%20the%20Muslim%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20a%20conversation%20(with%20India)%20saying%2C%20here%20are%20the%20imperfections%20in%20our%20democracy%2C%20what%20are%20the%20imperfections%20in%20your%20democracy%2C%20and%20how%20do%20we%20collectively%20advance%20democracy%20and%20human%20rights%2C%20I%20think%20is%20a%20more%20constructive%20approach%2C%26quot%3B%20Khanna%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBera%20said%20he%20agrees%20with%20Khanna.%20%26quot%3BI've%20said%20the%20same%20to%20the%20(Indian)%20foreign%20minister.%20If%20India%20loses%20its%20secular%20nation%2C%20it%20changes%20who%20she%20is%20as%20a%20country%20and%20how%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20views%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20a%20Trump%20presidency%20is%20not%20necessarily%20the%20same%20as%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20being%20in%20power.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20we%20still%20have%20a%20vibrant%20democracy%20here.%20We%20have%20a%20vibrant%20opposition%20party%20in%20the%20Democratic%20Party.%20We%20still%20believe%20in%20the%20freedom%20of%20the%20press%20and%20those%20are%20all%20things%20that%20I%20worry%20about%20India's%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20see%20what's%20happening%20to%20the%20freedom%20of%20the%20press.%20You're%20not%20really%20seeing%20a%20viable%20opposition%20party%20or%20it's%20being%20dismantled.%20The%20vibrant%20democracy%20has%20to%20have%20all%20of%20those%20things%2C%20freedom%20of%20speech%2C%20freedom%20of%20the%20press%2C%20the%20ability%20to%20push%20back.%20I%20hope%20you%20don't%20ever%20see%20a%20second%20Trump%20presidency.%20But%20if%20that%20were%20to%20happen%2C%20you%20will%20see%20our%20democracy%20survive%20the%20first%20time%2C%20push%20back%2C%20and%20our%20democracy%20will%20survive.%20I%20certainly%20hope%20India's%20democracy%20survives%2C%26quot%3B%20Bera%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJayapal%20said%20she%20agrees%20with%20both%20Bera%20and%20Khanna.%20%26quot%3BThe%20only%20thing%20I%20would%20add%20is%20that%20I%20think%20we%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20critique%20our%20own%20country's%20imperfections%20and%20any%20other%20country's%20imperfections.%20That's%20actually%20our%20job%20in%20Congress.%20We%20shouldn't%20lecture%2C%20I%20agree%20with%20Roe%20(Khanna).%20But%20we%20do%20have%20to%20think%20about%20all%20of%20the%20United%20States'%20interests.%20That%20is%20economic%2C%20for%20sure.%20India%20is%20an%20important%20partner%20for%20us.%20It's%20an%20important%20partner%20because%20of%20other%20regional%20dynamics%20as%20well%20and%20global%20dynamics%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20also%20important%20for%20us%20to%20think%20about%20our%20values.%20Just%20like%20we%20criticize%20the%20Chinese%20government%20for%20the%20treatment%20of%20Uyghurs%20or%20any%20other%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%20we%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20also%20look%20at%20what's%20happening%20in%20India%20and%20call%20attention%20to%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20that%20I%20have%20been%20called%20a%20bad%20Indian%20and%20all%20kinds%20of%20other%20things%20for%20raising%20these.%20But%20I%20would%20just%20say%20I'm%20not%20backing%20away%20from%20that%20because%20those%20are%20the%20values%20of%20the%20United%20States.%20Those%20are%20my%20values.%20I%20don't%20think%20it%20means%20that%20you%20don't%20appreciate%20or%20like%20or%20want%20a%20partnership%20between%20India%20and%20the%20United%20States%20to%20raise%20legitimate%20concerns%20about%20freedom%20of%20religion%2C%20freedom%20of%20the%20press%2C%20and%20all%20of%20the%20other%20things%20that%20we%20are%20seeing%20in%20India%20any%20more%20than%20if%20we%20raise%20it%20here%20it%20means%20somehow%20that%20we're%20bad%20Americans.%20No%2C%20that%20is%20our%20job%20to%20be%20moving%20towards%20a%20more%20perfect%20union%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20with%20all%20of%20our%20global%20partnerships%2C%26quot%3B%20Jayapal%20asserted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThanedar%20said%20he%20favours%20a%20strong%20India-US%20relationship.%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20a%20strong%20US-India%20relationship.%20India%20historically%20has%20been%20playing%20both%20sides%2C%20Russia%20and%20US.%20But%20it's%20time%20for%20India%20to%20commit%20to%20a%20strong%20friendship%20with%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20that's%20something%20that%20I%20want%20to%20work%20on.%20The%20United%20States%20has%20to%20recognize%20India's%20power%2C%20its%20economic%20power%2C%20and%20India%20remains%20the%20best%20solution%20to%20counteract%20China's%20aggression.%20So%2C%20I'm%20just%20working%20on%20a%20strong%20India-US%20relationship%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715908140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2018-09%2Fq35u6gic_india-us-flags-reuters_625x300_18_September_18.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flecturing-india-on-human-rights-wont-work-indian-american-lawmakers-5680848%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Reiterating%20that%20they%20would%20continue%20to%20raise%20the%20issue%20of%20human%20rights%20in%20India%20with%20its%20leadership%2C%20Indian%20American%20lawmakers%20on%20Thursday%2C%20however%2C%20said%20that%20lecturing%20New%20Delhi%20on%20this%20issue%20is%20unlikely%20to%20work%20and%20they%20favoured%20entering%20into%20a%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flecturing-india-on-human-rights-wont-work-indian-american-lawmakers-5680848%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flecturing-india-on-human-rights-wont-work-indian-american-lawmakers-5680848%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flecturing-india-on-human-rights-wont-work-indian-american-lawmakers-5680848%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Young%20Sheldon%E2%80%99%20Series%20Finale%20Breakdown%3A%20Why%20Jim%20Parsons%20and%20Mayim%20Bialik%20Became%20a%20Bigger%20Part%20of%20the%20Ending%2C%20Reba%E2%80%99s%20Return%20and%20When%20the%20Spinoff%20Will%20Pick%20Up%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715907660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FYoungSheldon.seriesfinale.1.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariet